```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) |> replace("-" => "_", " " => "_")
end
```

This function first lowers the case of the string using `lowercase`, then strips any leading or trailing whitespaces with `strip`. Finally, it replaces both spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace`. The result is a column name that is all lowercase, has no leading or trailing spaces, and has internal spaces replaced with underscores.
